title: Uber Is Said to Select Morgan Stanley to Lead Public Offering
text: Dec.11 -- Uber Technologies Inc. has selected Morgan Stanley to lead its public offering next year, according to two people familiar with the matter, meaning the investment bank will reap a larger share of the fees associated with a listing valuing the company at as much as $120 billion. Bloomberg's Tom Giles and Emma Chandra have more on "Bloomberg Markets: Balance of Power."

title: Lyft IPO price range now $70 to $72
text: CNBC's Deirdre Bosa reports on Lyft's recent increase in its expected IPO price range.

title: Lyft increases IPO range, expects to charge $70 to $72 a share
text: Lyft Inc. increased the amount it expects to charge for shares in its initial public offering Wednesday afternoon, raising the expected range to $70 to $72 a share.

title: Casper Sleep reportedly hires underwriters for an IPO
text: CNBC's Rahel Solomon breaks down news that U.S. online mattress retailer Casper Sleep Inc is seeking to hire underwriters for an initial public offering, according to Reuters.

title: Q1 GDP tracking at 1.5 percent
text: CNBC's Steve Liesman joins the 'Fast Money Halftime Report' team to discuss what CNBC and Moody's Analytics are seeing for Q1 GDP.

title: Why this expert says the IPO market is a 'dangerous place'
text: Eric Hippeau, managing partner at Lerer Hippeau, and Larry Haverty, managing director at LJH Investment Advisors, joins "Squawk Alley" to look ahead at some of the biggest IPOs of 2019, and why they might not be the best investments.

title: Casper seeking underwriters for IPO
text: Melody Hahm, Heidi Cheung, Myles Udland and Dan Roberts of Yahoo Finance discuss the online mattress company Casper  which is seeking underwriters for its IPO.

title: How this portfolio manager is navigating market volatility
text: Bryant VanCronkhite, Wells Fargo portfolio manager, and Eric Marshall, Hodges Small Cap Fund portfolio manager, discuss the state of the markets and how they're navigating ongoing volatility with CNBC's "Squawk on the Street."

title: Market optimism rises in CNBC's All-America Economic Survey
text: CNBC's Steve Liesman breaks down new survey data from CNBC's All-America Economic Survey that shows Americans' confidence in the economy and markets are rising.

title: Watch CNBC's full interview with Senator Ted Cruz
text: Sen. Ted Cruz (R-Texas) joins "Squawk Box" to discuss the congressional hearing on the Boeing 737 Max crashes, the ACA court challenge, the Mueller report, and the future of space exploration.

title: The Lyft IPO: What You Need To Know
text: In the race to the U.S. markets, Lyft is about to lap Uber and other ride-hailing rivals.

title: US reportedly pushes Chinese owner of Grindr to divest the dating app
text: Chinese gaming company Beijing Kunlun Tech is seeking to sell Grindr after a U.S. government panel raised concerns about its ownership.

title: Watch Triton Research CEO explain his scoring system for tech IPO valuations
text: Rett Wallace, CEO and co-founder of Triton Research, joins "Squawk Box" to give his expertise on how investors should evaluate the highly anticipated tech IPOs.

title: Here's how economic confidence affects the markets
text: According to CNBC's All-America Economic Survey, half of all Americans believe the economy is in excellent or good shape.

title: Uber and Careem deal is 'hugely exciting' for the region, expert says | Capital Connection
text: Tom Hudson, managing director at Kestrel Global, discusses the significance of a deal between Uber and Careem in the Middle East.

title: Should investors avoid Lyft IPO?
text: Flynn Zito Capital Management's Doug Flynn on the Lyft IPO, the outlook for Apple and UPS' use of drones.

title: EU shuns US calls to ban Huawei from its future 5G networks
text: The European Union move comes despite U.S. pressure to boycott Huawei, citing fears of China using its equipment for espionage.
